    "data": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><span>This tiny box holds a fragment of religious scripture sacred to a particular deity. The box is worn by affixing it to a leather cord and tying it around your head just above your brow. You don&rsquo;t gain any benefit from the phylactery if you don&rsquo;t worship the affiliated deity. The phylactery grants you religious wisdom, which manifests as a +2 item bonus to Religion checks. Just before you perform an action that would be anathema to the phylactery&rsquo;s deity, the phylactery warns you of the potential transgression in time for you to change your mind.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Activate</strong> <span style=\"font-family: 'Pathfinder2eActions'; font-size: 1.8em; display: inline;\">A</span> envision; <strong>Frequency</strong> once per day; <strong>Effect</strong> You ask for guidance about a particular course of action, gaining the effects of an @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.41TZEjhO6D1nWw2X]{Augury} spell.</span></p>",
